There are multiple ways to use regions to make your searches more accurate and faster. The basic idea is that you can use regions (i.e. defined rectangles on the screen) to focus your search to a smaller area of the screen. If you can (for example) confine the search to one quadrant of the screen, the search will be faster and less likely to produce a false positive match.
A region is defined by four values. The four values define the upper left and lower right corners of a rectangle (measured in pixels) on the screen.
resolution, you specify the whole screen by the four values (0,0,1600,1200).
